AGI -&nbsp;<span><span><span> > Being considered as a resource. And not as a problem > The representatives of the Roma and Sinti Italian movement are asking for this next European Parliament >. That, precisely to raise awareness of Italian and institutional public opinion, promote for the first time electoral forums within the Roma fields.</span> The association Roma for democracy, with the Movement Kethane - Rom and Sinti for Italy, has in fact launched a series of meetings with candidates for the European elections > of the next 8 and 9 June 2024, within the Roma fields. The aim is to bring the aspiring europarlamentari<span> to dialogue with the camp residents, answering their questions and proposals. </span </span </span </span </span >
&nbsp;
<span><span><span>“It is the first time that such a thing happens – explains to AGI Dijana Pavlović>, </span> portavoce of the Movement Kethane Rom and Sinti for Italy <span>-. We are 6 million throughout the European Union, of which 2 million children. In practice a small country, like Denmark. At such a delicate historical stage, Europe should not afford to discard such an important number of people.” </span> The first event took place two days ago in Rome, in the field of Via dei Gordiani. To participate Vauro Senesi, designer and writer, lead candidate of <span>Pace Terra Dignità, the movement of Michele Santoro, Christian Raimo, teacher and writer, candidate among the ranks of Alleanza Verdi Sinistra</span>, and Marco Tarquinio, already director of the future and today in list with the Pd. </span></span></span>
&nbsp;
Approximately 50 people, many young people. The work was one of the themes most dealt with by the public, particularly women. They are concerned because children do not find employment and many inhabitants of the camp often have to hide their place of residence, because otherwise they are not hired. Racism episodes also only enter a bar or a supermarket. Instead, they are only eager to make a normal life.” The last case, according to what is reported by the same association, just yesterday on the occasion of the electoral forum, that it was necessary to carry out without the gazebo because the society from which it was to be rented would refuse to deliver it just because the event took place, in fact, inside a Roma field. Episodes that, however, do not desist the community from seeking its own space in society. </span </span </span </span </span >
